<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>Why Zipper Door Kits Matter</h2>

  <p>
    Without a proper door, greenhouse plastic must be lifted or removed to access plants. This reduces efficiency and can damage the structure over time.
  </p>

  <p>
    A zipper door creates a consistent entry point that maintains the integrity of the enclosure.
  </p>

  <p>
    It also helps control airflow and temperature more precisely.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>What Makes a Good Zipper Door Kit</h2>

  <h3>Strong Adhesive Backing</h3>
  <p>
    The adhesive must bond securely to plastic and resist peeling in heat and moisture.
  </p>

  <h3>Weather Resistance</h3>
  <p>
    Outdoor exposure requires materials that handle sun, wind, and temperature changes.
  </p>

  <h3>Smooth Zipper Operation</h3>
  <p>
    A reliable zipper reduces strain on the plastic and improves daily use.
  </p>

  <h3>Reinforced Edges</h3>
  <p>
    Prevents tearing where the door is opened and closed repeatedly.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="guideSection">
